<br>
To be honest, there is nothing there that gives ample support to the claims made here.  Yes, Raile did take leadership somehow, but the details behind why are still VERY unclear, and the 'why' is the very reason so many people are mad.<br>
<br>
I can note that some people are angry with Raile and some people seem to support her, but what does that mean?  I can note that Fallguy apparently started kicking a bunch of people out of the guild in a fit of rage, but what does that mean?<br>
<br>
It means there are two sides to this story, both here and on their message board.<br>
<br>
The question still lingers:  There is overwhelming, undeniable proof to refute the claim made by Raile to the GM for why she took the guild.  So why is the GM doing nothing?  It happened at the latest on August 2nd, and that was four days ago as of now.<br>
<br>
It would mean that either no GM has logged on in four days, or that the GM simply does not care for this problem any longer.<br>
<br>
If he does not care for the problem, he is either turning a blind eye to a very large problem (unlikely) or there is a stronger reason behind why he gave Raile the guild in the first place.<br>
<br>
Do I believe Raile did this terrible thing to a respectable person who stuck around longer than any other person could be expected to?  Based on reports of her bitchy and selfish personality from my sister, I certainly do not doubt it at all.  This seems to be one of the most despicable things done to someone that I have EVER come across in this game.<br>
<br>
I just want to clearly see what happened through the eyes of people who were involved.  I want to know what happened in the words of someone who was there.  No one on the KotEW message board really say in a direct manner what happened.<br>
<br>
I'm trying to view this from an objective stance.  I'm trying to give Raile what little benift of the doubt she has before crucifying her.<br>
<br>
The facts of the story we are told so far don't entirely add up.  Would you burn the witch when there is reasonable doubt yet to be had?  Apparently, many already have.<br>
<br>
I prefer to draw my own conclutions as based on facts and testimony... not believe every single word as told to me by someone who, apparently, was not involved at the time.   If Aailin comes forth and says he was present for everything... then it will be a different story, but he hasn't claimed anything of the sort.  Add to that the fact that is is apparently misinformed about some of the facts, and I have questions.<br>
<br>
This is a BIG accusation to throw out as far as EQ is concerned (again, one of the most horrible things possible in all respects!!), and it's not something that you should take lightly before passing judgement. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krogothbitterstar>KrogothBitterstar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/6/03 11:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3817.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Raile and the Knights of the Ebon Wolf..</span><hr size=1> Ok looks like I am one of the only people who were in KOTEW who is looking at this board so I will add my piece to this again. <br>
