<br>
So what are we missing?  Why did the GM switch leadership, and why won't he switch it back?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The reason she did this is not relevant, it is the fact that she did it at all which condemns her<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Would it continue to be irrelevant if it were uncovered that the GM gave leadership to Raile because he felt Fallguy was being undeservedly destructive to the guild and he had ample support to this claim?  No, it would not be.  The reason why the GM acted is everything.<br>
<br>
Are you against ALL forms of GM intervention to take leadership of a guild?  If you are not, it leads to conclude that you would feel there are reasons when it is justified, which counters your own point that the reason is not relevant.<br>
<br>
Are you kidding me?!  The reason Fallguy himself gave for why the people were kicked out of the guild was because he heard a RUMOR that they were leaving to another guild!  Sorry, and I'm sure that Fallguy is a nice guy and all (who else would stick around a one man guild for so long) but that is not the action of a good or responsible leader, and it would be actions I would think a GM could consider 'destructive for the guild'.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>known is that she went and had a GM give her back the guild that she founded, which they will do, and probably by their judegement, is what they have to do since she did found the guild<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> Accually, Cuellari would have been the founding leader, and if GMs do will give back guilds based on nothing more than founding leader (which is crap if they do!) then what claim does Raile have?  Or does it only have to be 'founding account'?  I don't ask this to drill you, and do so out of honest curiosity.  I don't mean to attack you or anyone, only to try and find out the truth.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Safron was/still was (Guild Leader), and Fall was an officer trying to rebuild the guild<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://kuboko.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/current_guild_rosta.htm" target="top">Note here the L next to Fallguy's name, as well as Safron's</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  Fallguy was more than an officer.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Also just because she founded the guild doesn't mean that she couldn't have been voted out. Some guilds have a voted on leadership<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> Voted when?  After Cuellari had already been leader?  First off, from the story Aailin gave, she was not voted out of leadership, she was simply never voted leader to begin with, and that is why she wanted revenge.  Second, from Fallguy himself, it seems Safron gained leadership because Cuellari left.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Safron would not give you back the leadership when you (Raile, Cuellari) left<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> That kind of crosses a line through the possibility that Cuellari was voted out of leadership.<br>
<br>
These statements do not refute the (strong) possibility that Raile did infact steal the guild four days ago, but it does directly contradict the claims Aailin made in intially bringing this topic here. It makes it seem like he does not fully know what happened.<br>
<br>
And yet his testimony is all anyone has concerning the stealing of this guild.<br>
<br>
That is my point. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aailin>Aailin </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 590<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/6/03 1:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3817.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   RE</span><hr size=1> Good point Leani so let me straigthen it out.<br>
